# Trivy CVE ignore list
#
# Format:
#   CVE-XXXX-XXXXX  # Reason. Accepted: YYYY-MM-DD  Review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Do not add entries without:
#   1. A documented reason
#   2. An accepted date
#   3. A review date (max 90 days out)
#
# ── Docker CLI binary (usr/local/bin/docker) ──────────────────────────────────
#
# The Docker static binary is baked into the backend image solely to run Nuclei
# containers during scanning. It is a dev/self-hosted convenience — it will be
# removed from the production image as part of the production hardening work
# (see backlog: "Remove Docker CLI from production image").
#
# These are all Go stdlib DoS CVEs in docker-29.4.3 (Go 1.26.2). Fixed in
# Go 1.26.3 but no Docker release with that Go version is available yet.
# Risk: low — the Docker CLI is invoked internally via subprocess, not exposed
# as a network service.
#
CVE-2026-33811  # Docker CLI Go stdlib: LookupCNAME DoS via long CNAME. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-08-12
CVE-2026-33814  # Docker CLI Go stdlib: HTTP/2 SETTINGS infinite loop DoS. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-08-12
CVE-2026-39820  # Docker CLI Go stdlib: ParseAddress DoS via crafted input. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-08-12
CVE-2026-39836  # Docker CLI Go stdlib: NUL byte panic (Windows-only). Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-08-12
CVE-2026-42499  # Docker CLI Go stdlib: consumePhrase DoS via pathological input. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-08-12
